article.headline: Ark.-Little Rock 74, Denver 68
article.story: DENVER (AP) -- Rashad Jones-Jenning scored 17 points and pulled down 12 rebounds as Arkansas-Little Rock beat Denver 74-68 in Sun Belt Conference action Thursday night. Denver (4-20, 3-11) led by a point at halftime but Arkansas-Little Rock opened the second half with a 21-8 run to take the lead for good. While Jones-Jennings recorded his 15th double-double of the season, De'Andre Eggins scored 19, Lekheythan Malone 16, and Terrance Akins added 12 for Arkansas-Little Rock (11-14, 6-8). DaShawn Walker led Denver with 22 points, while Tyler Bullock added 13.
